(263, '28', 'How does the priority valve in System 1 prioritize flight control services during landing gear retraction with electric pump power?', 'By shutting off the electric motor-driven pump', 'By diverting all hydraulic pressure to the flight controls', 'By providing minimum flow to the landing gear using accumulator pressure', 'The priority valve does not affect landing gear operation in this scenario.', 'c', 'By providing minimum flow to the landing gear using accumulator pressure', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(264, '29', 'What is the main function of the accumulator in the hydraulic system?', 'To maintain constant system pressure', 'To minimize pressure surges from the pumps', 'To isolate a malfunctioning hydraulic system', 'To store excess hydraulic fluid during engine shutdown', 'b', 'To minimize pressure surges from the pumps', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(265, '30', 'Based on the passage, which EICAS message indicates a complete loss of pressure in a hydraulic system?', 'HYD SYS 1 (2) FAIL', 'HYD SYS 1 (2) OVHT', 'E1 (2) HYD PUMP FAIL', 'HYD PUMP SELEC OFF', 'a', 'HYD SYS 1 (2) FAIL', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(266, '31', 'What component on the Hydraulic System Panel allows pilots to isolate a specific engine\'s hydraulic pump?', 'Electric Hydraulic Pump Control Knob', 'Hydraulic Page on MFD (Multi-Function Display)', 'ENGINE PUMP SHUTOFF BUTTON (guarded)', 'There is no control for isolating individual pumps.', 'c', 'ENGINE PUMP SHUTOFF BUTTON (guarded)', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(267, '32', 'When is the striped bar on the Engine Pump Shutoff Button illuminated?', 'When the associated electric hydraulic pump is selected to ON', 'Whenever the hydraulic system pressure is low (indicates a fault)', 'Only during pre - flight checks', 'The button has no illumination; it\'s a mechanical press (mentioned as \" guarded \").', 'd', 'The button has no illumination; it\'s a mechanical press (mentioned as \" guarded \").', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(268, '33', 'What are the three available settings for the Electric Hydraulic Pump Control Knob?', 'Low, Medium, High (for pump output)', 'OFF, AUTO, Emergency (not mentioned in passage)', 'OFF, AUTO, ON', 'Continuous, Standby, Manual', 'c', 'OFF, AUTO, ON', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(269, '34', 'In AUTO mode, under what condition will the electric hydraulic pump automatically turn on?', 'When the pilot presses the Engine Pump Shutoff Button', 'If the hydraulic fluid quantity drops below 1 liter', 'Whenever the airplane lands on the ground (not based on passage)', 'When the engine-driven pump pressure falls below 1600 psi or engine N2 falls below 56.4 %', 'd', 'When the engine-driven pump pressure falls below 1600 psi or engine N2 falls below 56.4 %', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(270, '35', 'How does the Fluid Quantity Indication on the MFD display the hydraulic fluid level?', 'Through a text message indicating \" Full \" or \" Low \"', 'Using a horizontal scale with a green pointer: green for full, amber for low', 'By displaying the exact volume in liters', 'The fluid level is not displayed on the MFD.', 'b', 'Using a horizontal scale with a green pointer: green for full, amber for low', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(271, '36', 'What color is the pointer on the Fluid Quantity Indication when the hydraulic fluid level is sufficient (more than 1 liter)?', 'Red', 'Blue', 'Green', 'The pointer color does not indicate fluid level.', 'c', 'Green', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(272, '37', 'What color are the digits on the Pressure Indication when the hydraulic system pressure is within the normal operating range (1300 to 3300 psi)?', 'White', 'Yellow', 'Green', 'The digit color does not indicate pressure range.', 'c', 'Green', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(273, '38', 'Based on the passage, how are the pilots informed about a malfunction with the hydraulic pressure data?', 'The pressure indication will display a specific error message.', 'An amber warning light will illuminate on the Hydraulic System Panel.', 'The pressure digits on the MFD will be replaced by amber dashes.', 'There is no specific indication for pressure data malfunction.', 'c', 'The pressure digits on the MFD will be replaced by amber dashes.', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(274, '39', 'What information does the Electric Pump Status on the MFD provide?', 'The current operating pressure of the electric hydraulic pump', 'The remaining time until the pump needs maintenance', 'Whether the electric pump is selected to ON or OFF', 'The N2 value of the engine associated with the electric pump', 'c', 'Whether the electric pump is selected to ON or OFF', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(275, '40', 'Based on the passage, can pilots directly control the engine-driven hydraulic pumps through a dedicated panel switch?', 'Yes, there is a separate ON / OFF switch for each engine-driven pump.', 'No, the engine - driven pumps operate automatically with the engines.', 'The passage does not mention controls for engine-driven pumps.', 'Engine - driven pump control is integrated with the Electric Hydraulic Pump Control Knob.', 'c', 'The passage does not mention controls for engine-driven pumps.', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(276, '41', 'What is the primary function of the hydraulic system in the EMB - 145?', 'Fuel delivery', 'Cabin pressurization', 'Actuation of flight control surfaces', 'Air conditioning', 'c', 'Actuation of flight control surfaces', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(277, '42', 'Which of the following is not a component of a typical hydraulic system?', 'Pump', 'Actuator', 'Reservoir', 'Spark plug', 'd', 'Spark plug', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(278, '43', 'What principle does a hydraulic system operate on?', 'Newton’s Third Law', 'Pascal’s Law', 'Bernoulli’s Principle', 'Archimedes’ Principle', 'b', 'Pascal’s Law', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(279, '44', 'What is the typical operating pressure of an aircraft hydraulic system?', '500 PSI', '1000 PSI', '3000 PSI', '5000 PSI', 'c', '3000 PSI', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(280, '45', 'What happens if the hydraulic pressure in the system is lost?', 'The aircraft will lose all electrical power', 'The aircraft will not be able to communicate with air traffic control', 'The aircraft may lose control of certain flight control surfaces', 'The aircraft will not be able to maintain altitude', 'c', 'The aircraft may lose control of certain flight control surfaces', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(281, '46', 'What is the purpose of the hydraulic reservoir in the system?', 'To generate hydraulic pressure', 'To cool the hydraulic fluid', 'To store the hydraulic fluid', 'To act as a backup power source', 'c', 'To store the hydraulic fluid', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(282, '47', 'What is the function of the hydraulic actuator?', 'To store hydraulic fluid', 'To generate hydraulic pressure', 'To convert hydraulic pressure into mechanical motion', 'To control the flow of hydraulic fluid', 'c', 'To convert hydraulic pressure into mechanical motion', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(283, '48', 'What can cause a loss of hydraulic pressure in the system?', 'A drop in outside air temperature', 'A leak in the hydraulic lines', 'A change in altitude', 'A failure of the aircraft’s electrical system', 'b', 'A leak in the hydraulic lines', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(284, '49', 'What is the function of the hydraulic fluid in the system?', 'To provide electrical insulation', 'To cool the aircraft’s engines', 'To transmit power', 'To lubricate the aircraft’s engines', 'c', 'To transmit power', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(285, '50', 'What would happen if the hydraulic fluid overheats?', 'The fluid would freeze', 'The fluid could lose its ability to transmit power', 'The fluid would turn into a gas', 'The fluid would become more viscous', 'b', 'The fluid could lose its ability to transmit power', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(286, '51', 'Why is it important to regularly maintain the hydraulic system?', 'To ensure the aircraft looks clean', 'To prevent the aircraft from becoming too heavy', 'To prevent system failures and ensure safe operation', 'To keep the aircraft’s paint from peeling', 'c', 'To prevent system failures and ensure safe operation', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(287, '52', 'What is the role of the hydraulic pump in the system?', 'To store the hydraulic fluid', 'To generate hydraulic pressure', 'To cool the hydraulic fluid', 'To act as a backup power source', 'b', 'To generate hydraulic pressure', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(288, '53', 'What could be a sign of a problem with the hydraulic system?', 'The aircraft is flying too fast', 'The aircraft’s engines are too loud', 'The aircraft’s control surfaces are not responding properly', 'The aircraft’s lights are not working.', 'c', 'The aircraft’s control surfaces are not responding properly', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(289, '54', 'What is the purpose of the hydraulic accumulator in the system?', 'To generate hydraulic pressure', 'To cool the hydraulic fluid', 'To act as a backup power source', 'To store pressurized hydraulic fluid', 'd', 'To store pressurized hydraulic fluid', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(290, '55', 'What type of fluid is typically used in an aircraft hydraulic system?', 'Water', 'Specialized hydraulic fluid', 'Engine oil', 'Air', 'b', 'Specialized hydraulic fluid', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(291, '56', 'Why is it important for the hydraulic fluid to be incompressible?', 'To prevent the fluid from overheating', 'To make the fluid lighter', 'To allow the fluid to transmit power effectively', 'To prevent the fluid from leaking', 'c', 'To allow the fluid to transmit power effectively', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(292, '57', 'What is one of the main advantages of a hydraulic system over a mechanical system?', 'Hydraulic systems are lighter', 'Hydraulic systems are cheaper', 'Hydraulic systems can transmit larger forces', 'Hydraulic systems are easier to install', 'c', 'Hydraulic systems can transmit larger forces', 'ERJ-145', 'hydraulic', 'pilot'),
(293, '1', 'How are the extension / retraction, steering and braking functions of the EMB - 145 landing gear controlled?', 'Manually by the pilots', 'Hydraulically assisted, mechanically controlled, and electronically monitored', 'Hydraulically assisted, electronically controlled, and pneumatically monitored', 'Hydraulically assisted, electronically controlled, and electronically monitored', 'd', 'Hydraulically assisted, electronically controlled, and electronically monitored', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(294, '2', 'What system determines whether the aircraft is on the ground or airborne?', 'The pilots based on visual cues', 'A weight – on - wheel system with proximity switches', 'The airspeed indicator', 'The landing gear lever position', 'd', 'The landing gear lever position', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(295, '3', 'How many weight-on-wheel proximity switches are used in the EMB - 145 landing gear system?', 'One', 'Two', 'Three', '5', 'd', '5', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(296, '4', 'In case of a single faulty proximity switch signal, how many remaining signals need to agree for the air / ground output to be valid?', 'All remaining signals must agree', 'None of the remaining signals need to agree', 'At least two of the remaining three signals need to agree', 'At least three of the remaining four signals need to agree', 'c', 'At least two of the remaining three signals need to agree', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `question_number`, `question`, `option_a`, `option_b`, `option_c`, `option_d`, `correct_option`, `correct_answer`, `aircraft`, `course`, `target_audience`) VALUES
(297, '5', 'What is the primary function of the Landing Gear Electronic Unit (LGEU)?', 'To provide hydraulic pressure for landing gear operation', 'To process weight-on-wheel switch signals and control gear status', 'To activate the emergency landing gear extension system', 'To house the landing gear retraction motor', 'b', 'To process weight-on-wheel switch signals and control gear status', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(298, '6', 'What happens if there is disagreement between the two remaining weight – on - wheel switch signals?', 'The landing gear automatically extends', 'The aircraft experiences a partial loss of braking power', 'The LGEU de-energizes the channels and provides a default output signal', 'The pilots receive a visual warning light', 'c', 'The LGEU de-energizes the channels and provides a default output signal', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(299, '7', 'What powers the retraction and extension of the EMB - 145 landing gear?', 'Electric motors', 'Pneumatic system', 'Hydraulic system 1', 'Pilot muscle power', 'c', 'Hydraulic system 1', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(300, '8', 'What component helps maintain hydraulic pressure during gear operation?', 'Landing Gear Lever', 'Accumulator', 'Nose Gear Door Solenoid Valve', 'Uplock box', 'b', 'Accumulator', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(301, '9', 'How do the main landing gear doors function in relation to the gear itself?', 'The doors remain closed on the ground and open in flight.', 'The doors open automatically when the gear retracts and close manually when extended.', 'Each main gear leg is mechanically linked to its respective door, which opens when the gear is down and closes when retracted.', 'The nose landing gear doors control the opening and closing of the main landing gear doors.', 'c', 'Each main gear leg is mechanically linked to its respective door, which opens when the gear is down and closes when retracted.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(302, '10', 'How is landing gear retraction commanded?', 'By weight – on - wheel sensors', 'Through the Landing Gear Lever positioned to UP', 'Automatically by the airspeed indicator', 'By a dedicated electrical override switch', 'b', 'Through the Landing Gear Lever positioned to UP', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(303, '11', 'What prevents accidental landing gear retraction while on the ground?', 'The Landing Gear Electro valve', 'The air/ground system with a locking solenoid in the lever', 'The proximity switches in the uplock boxes', 'A manual locking pin on the Landing Gear Lever', 'b', 'The air/ground system with a locking solenoid in the lever', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(304, '12', 'How does the normal landing gear extension process work?', 'The pilot pulls the free-fall lever.', 'The Landing Gear Lever is positioned to DOWN, pressurizing the uplock actuators first.', 'The electrical override system bypasses the LGEU entirely.', 'Gear position is indicated on the EICAS display, triggering automatic extension.', 'b', 'The Landing Gear Lever is positioned to DOWN, pressurizing the uplock actuators first.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(305, '13', 'What is the purpose of the electrical override system for landing gear extension?', 'It\'s the normal landing gear extension procedure.', 'It\'s used to retract the gear after a failed extension attempt.', 'It provides an alternative extension method in case of normal extension failure.', 'It resets the air/ground system for a future landing.', 'c', 'It provides an alternative extension method in case of normal extension failure.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(306, '14', 'Where is the electrical override control switch located?', 'On the main instrument panel', 'Inside the free - fall lever compartment beside the copilot\'s seat', 'On a dedicated overhead panel', 'It\'s not a physical switch, but a digital command on the EICAS display.', 'b', 'Inside the free - fall lever compartment beside the copilot\'s seat', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(307, '15', 'What is the final step when using the electrical override for landing gear extension?', 'The pilot must exit the free-fall lever compartment.', 'The override switch is automatically reset to the normal position after extension', 'The system requires a manual depressurization of the hydraulic lines.', 'The switch needs to be held continuously throughout the extension process.', 'b', 'The override switch is automatically reset to the normal position after extension', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(308, '16', 'Describe the free - fall landing gear extension.', 'It\'s the preferred method for landing gear extension during normal operations.', 'It involves deploying a parachute to slow the gear descent.', 'This is the last resort option used if both normal and electrical override extensions fail', 'The free-fall lever releases a compressed air reservoir to forcefully extend the gear.', 'c', 'This is the last resort option used if both normal and electrical override extensions fail', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(309, '17', 'What action does the free - fall landing gear lever perform?', 'Activates a parachute for the landing gear', 'Directly extends the landing gear', 'Mechanically actuates the Free-Fall Selector Valve and unlocks uplocks', 'Provides hydraulic pressure to the landing gear system', 'c', 'Mechanically actuates the Free-Fall Selector Valve and unlocks uplocks', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(310, '18', 'What happens to the landing gear hydraulic lines after free - fall lever activation?', 'They remain pressurized.', 'They are connected to the return line, depressurizing the system.', 'They are isolated from both the pressure and return lines.', 'They are filled with compressed air.', 'b', 'They are connected to the return line, depressurizing the system.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(311, '19', 'What is the purpose of side-slipping the airplane after free - fall gear deployment?', 'To improve pilot visibility', 'To create additional lift for the gear', 'To help lock a main gear leg that didn\'t engage the down lock', 'To slow the descent speed of the airplane', 'c', 'To help lock a main gear leg that didn\'t engage the down lock', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(312, '20', 'How long does the free - fall lever stay locked after activation?', 'It unlocks automatically after a set time.', 'It remains locked until reset by a dedicated switch.', 'It stays locked until the landing gear is down and locked.', 'It can be manually unlocked at any time.', 'c', 'It stays locked until the landing gear is down and locked.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(313, '21', 'Under what primary condition does the landing gear warning sound?', 'Whenever the landing gear lever is not in the down position', 'If the airplane is on the ground and the gear is not down', 'When the airplane is in landing configuration with gear unlocked', 'If there is a malfunction detected in the landing gear system', 'c', 'When the airplane is in landing configuration with gear unlocked', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(314, '22', 'What are the three specific conditions that can trigger the landing gear warning at an altitude below 1,200 feet?', 'Radio altitude malfunction, flap position below 10 degrees, and thrust levers at idle', 'Radio altitude malfunction (or unavailable), flap position below 22 degrees, and one engine inoperative or thrust lever below 59 degrees', 'Any flap position below 45 degrees and thrust levers below idle on both engines', 'Landing gear lever not in the down position, airspeed below approach speed, and engine anti - ice activated', 'b', 'Radio altitude malfunction (or unavailable), flap position below 22 degrees, and one engine inoperative or thrust lever below 59 degrees', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(315, '23', 'What happens if the radio altimeter malfunctions and the landing gear warning activates below 1,200 feet with flaps below 22 degrees?', 'The warning cannot be silenced.', 'The warning can be silenced using the Landing Gear Warning Cutout Button.', 'The button only works if the thrust levers are advanced.', 'The system automatically resets after the airplane climbs above 1,200 feet.', 'b', 'The warning can be silenced using the Landing Gear Warning Cutout Button.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(316, '24', 'In what scenario can the landing gear warning voice message not be canceled?', 'When the flap selector lever is set between 22 and 45 degrees', 'If the radio altimeter is malfunctioning and the flaps are below 22 degrees', 'Whenever the landing gear lever is not in the down and locked position', 'With the radio altimeter functioning normally and flaps set at 45 degrees or higher', 'b', 'If the radio altimeter is malfunctioning and the flaps are below 22 degrees', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(317, '25', 'What does the illuminated amber bar inside the Landing Gear Warning Cutout Button indicate?', 'A system fault with the landing gear warning system', 'That the radio altimeter is no longer malfunctioning', 'The landing gear has successfully been extended and locked', 'The button requires replacement due to a malfunction', 'b', 'That the radio altimeter is no longer malfunctioning', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(318, '26', 'Under what circumstances will the illuminated amber bar in the Landing Gear Warning Cutout Button turn off?', 'If the radio altimeter is repaired', 'Manually pressing the button again', 'When the landing gear warning conditions are no longer met', 'After a pre-determined amount of time has elapsed', 'c', 'When the landing gear warning conditions are no longer met', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(319, '27', 'How does the EICAS (Electronic Integrated Cockpit Alerting System) display landing gear position?', 'Through a single green or red light', 'With individual boxes for each landing gear', 'Only by text messages on the MFD (Multi - Function Display)', 'There is no dedicated landing gear position display on the EICAS.', 'b', 'With individual boxes for each landing gear', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(320, '28', 'What does a green DN label inside a green box on the EICAS signify?', 'Landing gear lever disagreement', 'Landing gear unlocked and in transit', 'Landing gear retracted and locked', 'Landing gear down and locked', 'd', 'Landing gear down and locked', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(321, '29', 'How does the EICAS indicate that the landing gear is moving between positions (in transit)?', 'By a flashing green DN label', 'With a solid white UP label', 'Through a red and black cross - hatched box', 'There is no specific indication for gear in transit.', 'c', 'Through a red and black cross - hatched box', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(322, '30', 'What does a red and black cross-hatched box or a red label (UP or DN) inside a red box on the EICAS indicate?', 'Landing gear down and locked', 'Landing gear malfunction', 'Landing gear lever disagreement (not in selected position)', 'Emergency brake system engaged', 'c', 'Landing gear lever disagreement (not in selected position)', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(323, '31', 'Besides the EICAS, where else is the landing gear down and locked status displayed?', 'On the captain\'s control panel', 'Through a dedicated annunciator light', 'On the Radio Management Unit (RMU) with a green \" LG DOWN LOCKED \" message', 'There is no redundant landing gear status display.', 'c', 'On the Radio Management Unit (RMU) with a green \" LG DOWN LOCKED \" message', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(324, '32', 'How many brake systems does the EMB - 145 have?', 'One main hydraulically controlled system', 'Two independent electronic braking systems', 'Three separate systems: normal, emergency, and gear retraction', 'The braking system is integrated with the anti - skid system.', 'c', 'Three separate systems: normal, emergency, and gear retraction', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(325, '33', 'Which hydraulic systems supply power to the normal braking system?', 'Only hydraulic system 1', 'Only hydraulic system 2', 'Both hydraulic systems 1 and 2', 'An independent electric motor - driven pump', 'c', 'Both hydraulic systems 1 and 2', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(326, '34', 'How is normal braking controlled by the pilot?', 'Through a handbrake lever', 'By pressing buttons on the control panel', 'With the rudder pedals', 'It\'s automatic and pilot - controlled only in emergencies.', 'c', 'With the rudder pedals', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(327, '35', 'What system is used for emergency braking?', 'The normal braking system with increased pedal pressure', 'A dedicated electronically controlled emergency brake system', 'The gear – retracting – in - flight braking system', 'A mechanically actuated emergency / parking brake handle', 'd', 'A mechanically actuated emergency / parking brake handle', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(328, '36', 'Where can the pilot monitor brake temperature on the EMB - 145?', 'Through a dedicated temperature gauge on the instrument panel', 'On the EICAS display', 'Not displayed, pilots rely on pedal feel for temperature awareness.', 'On the MFD Hydraulic Page', 'd', 'On the MFD Hydraulic Page', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(329, '37', 'How does the pilot control the normal braking system?', 'Through a handbrake lever', 'By pressing buttons on the control panel', 'With the rudder pedals', 'It\'s automatic and pilot - controlled only in emergencies.', 'c', 'With the rudder pedals', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(330, '38', 'How many independent hydraulic systems provide power to the normal braking system?', 'One main hydraulic system', 'Two independent hydraulic systems', 'Three separate hydraulic systems', 'The system is electrically powered.', 'b', 'Two independent hydraulic systems', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(331, '39', 'How does the Brake Control Unit (BCU) determine the required brake pressure?', 'It receives signals from the landing gear position sensors.', 'It uses a pre-programmed braking profile based on airspeed.', 'It monitors pilot input through the rudder pedal position transducers.', 'The BCU relies solely on wheel speed sensor data.', 'c', 'It monitors pilot input through the rudder pedal position transducers.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(332, '40', 'Which Brake Control Valves (BCVs) control the outboard main landing gear wheels?', 'BCVs 1 and 2', 'BCVs 2 and 3', 'BCVs 1 and 4', 'All four BCVs control both inboard and outboard wheels.', 'c', 'BCVs 1 and 4', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(333, '41', 'What is the power source for the hydraulic system 1 that controls the outboard brakes?', 'The ESS DC BUS 1 only', 'The hydraulic system 2', 'Both the hydraulic system 1 and the ESS DC BUS 1', 'An independent electric motor - driven pump', 'c', 'Both the hydraulic system 1 and the ESS DC BUS 1', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(334, '42', 'How does the BCU monitor the performance of the braking system?', 'Through pilot pedal feel feedback', 'By receiving signals from pressure and wheel speed transducers', 'It relies solely on the Brake Control Valve positions.', 'The BCU only monitors the hydraulic system status.', 'b', 'By receiving signals from pressure and wheel speed transducers', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(335, '43', 'What information does the BCU receive besides pedal position and wheel data?', 'Engine thrust lever position and airspeed', 'Landing gear position and condition, air / ground status, and hydraulic system status', 'Flap position and altitude', 'Rudder pedal deflection angle and pilot weight', 'b', 'Landing gear position and condition, air / ground status, and hydraulic system status', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(336, '44', 'How does the EICAS display indicate a problem with the normal braking system?', 'By a single warning light', 'With specific messages for single or paired brake failures', 'There is no dedicated EICAS display for brake system faults.', 'Only the Brake Control Unit (BCU) detects and manages brake issues.', 'b', 'With specific messages for single or paired brake failures', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(337, '45', 'What action does the BCU take in case of a hydraulic system failure affecting the brakes?', 'It automatically applies maximum braking force.', 'It shuts down the affected hydraulic system through shutoff valves.', 'It diverts hydraulic pressure from the unaffected system to compensate.', 'The BCU relies on pilot reaction to the system failure.', 'b', 'It shuts down the affected hydraulic system through shutoff valves.', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(338, '46', 'What are three protective functions included in the normal braking system?', 'Rudder deflection limiter, engine power reduction, and sideslip prevention', 'Anti - skid protection, locked wheel protection, and touch - down protection', 'Spoiler deployment, elevator trim adjustment, and automatic rudder control', 'Gear retraction override activation, landing gear warning system reset, and thrust reverser inhibition', 'b', 'Anti - skid protection, locked wheel protection, and touch - down protection', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
(339, '47', 'What is the primary function of the anti - skid protection system?', 'To automatically apply maximum braking pressure', 'To regulate brake pressure for optimal stopping power and prevent skidding', 'To provide feedback to the pilot about runway surface conditions', 'To disengage the brakes momentarily during gear retraction', 'b', 'To regulate brake pressure for optimal stopping power and prevent skidding', 'ERJ-145', 'landing_gear', 'pilot'),
