(729, '321', 'During ground operations, which source provides bleed air for the pneumatic system?', 'APU (Auxiliary Power Unit)', 'Engine bleed valves', 'Ram air system', 'Ground air starter Machin', 'a', 'APU (Auxiliary Power Unit)', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(730, '322', 'What safety precautions should be taken when working on the pneumatic system of the EMB - 145?', 'Wear hearing protection due to high noise levels', 'Avoid contact with hot surfaces', 'Use insulated tools to prevent electrical shock', 'All of the above', 'd', 'All of the above', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(731, '323', 'Which type of valve prevents excessive pressure buildup in the pneumatic system?', 'Pressure relief valve', 'Check valve', 'Solenoid valve', 'Flow control valve', 'a', 'Pressure relief valve', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(732, '324', 'What is the purpose of the check valve in the pneumatic system?', 'To regulate airflow', 'To prevent reverse flow', 'To control temperature', 'To filter the air', 'b', 'To prevent reverse flow', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(733, '325', 'How is the pneumatic system affected during an engine start?', 'Bleed air is shut off', 'Cabin pressure decreases', 'Air conditioning packs are turned off', 'Water separator is bypassed', 'a', 'Bleed air is shut off', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(734, '326', 'What is the purpose of the pneumatic duct leak detection system?', 'To monitor cabin pressure', 'To detect leaks in the pneumatic ducting', 'To regulate airflow', 'To prevent ice formation', 'b', 'To detect leaks in the pneumatic ducting', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(735, '327', 'What does the Temperature Control Knob do in the EMB - 145 air conditioning system?', 'Adjusts cabin lighting', 'Regulates cabin temperature', 'Controls engine bleed air flow', 'Manages hydraulic pressure', 'b', 'Regulates cabin temperature', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(736, '328', 'What warning message is displayed if bleed air temperature downstream of the heat exchanger is too high?', 'BLD 1 (2) OVTEMP', 'BLEED HIGH TEMP', 'EXCHANGER OVERHEAT', 'AIRFLOW WARNING', 'a', 'BLD 1 (2) OVTEMP', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(737, '329', 'How does the Temperature Control Knob work in the EMB - 145 air conditioning system?', 'AUTO: knob pressed in, range from - 10 to 50 °C', 'MANUAL: knob pulled out; no range', 'ATTD: counterclockwise detent; gives FA control of cabin', 'All of the above', 'd', 'All of the above', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(738, '330', 'How does the Gasper Air Sub - System contribute to ice protection in the EMB - 145?', 'It heats the wings', 'It prevents ice buildup on the windshield', 'It cools the leading edges', 'It supplies warm air to the gasper outlets.', 'd', 'It supplies warm air to the gasper outlets.', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(739, '331', 'When is a red BLD 1 (2) OVTEMP warning message displayed?', 'When the cabin temperature is too high.', 'When the bleed air temperature downstream of the heat exchanger is too high.', 'When the oxygen system pressure is low.', 'When the air conditioning system malfunctions.', 'b', 'When the bleed air temperature downstream of the heat exchanger is too high.', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(740, '332', 'What does the amplified procedure for air conditioning set involve during the receiving check?', 'Adjusting the cabin temperature.', 'Checking the air conditioning system for leaks.', 'Ensuring proper airflow.', 'None of the above.', 'b', 'Checking the air conditioning system for leaks.', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(741, '333', 'What is the purpose of the air conditioning system in the EMB - 145?', 'To provide fresh air to the cockpit.', 'To regulate cabin temperature and humidity.', 'To cool the engines during takeoff.', 'To pressurize the cabin.', 'b', 'To regulate cabin temperature and humidity.', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(742, '334', 'Which component of the EMB - 145 air conditioning system provides cooling for the avionics bay?', 'The recirculation fans.', 'The heat exchanger.', 'The air cycle machine.', 'The temperature control knob.', 'b', 'The heat exchanger.', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(743, '335', 'What is the purpose of the air cycle machine (ACM) in the EMB - 145?', 'To cool the cabin air.', 'To pressurize the cabin.', 'To regulate the temperature of the bleed air.', 'To provide fresh air to the cockpit.', 'c', 'To regulate the temperature of the bleed air.', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(744, '336', 'During ground operations, which source provides air for the air conditioning system in the EMB - 145?', 'The ACM.', 'The engines.', 'The ground air supply.', 'The recirculation fans.', 'c', 'The ground air supply.', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(745, '337', 'What is the maximum differential pressure in the EMB - 145 pressurization system?', '8.4 PSI', '7.8 PSI', '9.4 PSI', '6.4 PSI', 'a', '8.4 PSI', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(746, '338', 'What is the primary purpose of the pressurization system in the EMB - 145?', 'To provide thrust', 'To maintain a comfortable and safe environment in the cabin at high altitudes', 'To cool the engines', 'To assist in fuel combustion', 'b', 'To maintain a comfortable and safe environment in the cabin at high altitudes', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(747, '339', 'What component controls the cabin pressure in the EMB - 145?', 'The Auxiliary Power Unit (APU)', 'The Environmental Control System (ECS)', 'The Hydraulic System', 'The Fuel System', 'b', 'The Environmental Control System (ECS)', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(748, '340', 'What happens if the cabin pressure becomes too high?', 'The engines will shut down', 'The landing gear will deploy', 'The cabin pressure relief valves will open', 'The aircraft will descend automatically', 'c', 'The cabin pressure relief valves will open', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(749, '341', 'How is the cabin altitude usually maintained in the EMB - 145?', 'By adjusting the engine throttle', 'By opening and closing the outflow valve', 'By changing the wing flaps position', 'By adjusting the landing gear', 'b', 'By opening and closing the outflow valve', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(750, '342', 'What is the source of pressurization in the EMB - 145?', 'The engines', 'The wings', 'The landing gears', 'The tail', 'a', 'The engines', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(751, '343', 'What is the function of the outflow valve in the ERJ - 145 pressurization system?', 'To let air into the cabin', 'To let air out of the cabin', 'To cool the cabin', 'To heat the cabin', 'b', 'To let air out of the cabin', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
(752, '344', 'What would happen if the pressurization system fails at high altitude?', 'The oxygen masks would deploy', 'The engines would shut down', 'The landing gear would deploy', 'The aircraft would automatically land', 'a', 'The oxygen masks would deploy', 'ERJ-145', 'pneumatic_aircondition_pressurization', 'pilot'),
