(5100, '41027', 'The normal power source for the Battery Charger is the AC Ground Service Bus, with provisions for automatic switching to', 'The No. 2 Main Bus', 'The No. 1 Main Bus', 'Either Transfer Bus', '', 'a', 'The No. 2 Main Bus', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5101, '41028', 'Pulling up an engine fire handle will', 'Trip the associated Generator Control Relay only', 'Trip the associated Generator Control Relay and Breaker', 'Trip the associated Generator Control Relay and disconnects the Generator Drive', '', 'b', 'Trip the associated Generator Control Relay and Breaker', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5102, '41029', 'If the Battery switch is selected OFF, the airstairs can be lowered from the outside', 'By using the STANDBY system', 'By using the NORMAL system with ground power plugged in', 'By using the STANDBY system, but can only be raised again by use of the NORMAL system', '', 'a', 'By using the STANDBY system', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5103, '41030', 'To have all three Generators (APU and engines) on-line simultaneously', 'Is not possible', 'Is possible on the ground only', 'Is possible in flight only', '', 'a', 'Is not possible', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5104, '41031', 'With an engine Generator switch selected OFF and the associated engine is running, the voltage of that generator will read', '115 volts', 'Approximately 3 volts', 'Residual volts when the residual volts switch is pressed', '', 'c', 'Residual volts when the residual volts switch is pressed', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5105, '41032', 'To connect the External Ground power to the aircraft\'s Generator busses', 'The Bus Transfer switch must be in the AUTO position', 'The Battery switch must be OFF', 'The Battery switch must be ON', '', 'c', 'The Battery switch must be ON', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5106, '41033', 'Standby D.C. power is normally supplied from', 'The Hot Battery Bus', 'The Battery Bus', 'DC Bus No. 1', '', 'c', 'DC Bus No. 1', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5107, '41034', 'Failure of the No. 1 Generator Bus will', 'Will cause failure of the System A Electric hydraulic pump', 'Have no effect on either electric hydraulic pump', 'Will cause failure of the System B Electric hydraulic pump', '', 'c', 'Will cause failure of the System B Electric hydraulic pump', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5108, '41035', 'Placing the BUS TRANS switch to \'OFF\' inflight with both generators operating and connected', 'Isolates the transfer busses by preventing operation of the bus transfer relay, opens the TR 1 and 2 disconnect relays and prevents connection of the battery to the Static Inverter', 'Isolates the transfer busses by preventing operation of the bus transfer relay, opens the TR 3 disconnect relay and prevents connection of the battery charger to its alternate power source ( Main Bus 2 )', 'Isolates the transfer busses by preventing operation of the bus transfer relay and opens the TR 3 disconnect relay only', '', 'a', 'Isolates the transfer busses by preventing operation of the bus transfer relay, opens the TR 1 and 2 disconnect relays and prevents connection of the battery to the Static Inverter', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5109, '41036', 'Which of the following statements is correct', 'TR 3 normally backs up TR 1 and TR 2 provided that the BUS TRANS switch is in OFF', 'TR 3 backs up TR 2 only', 'TR 3 normally backs up TR 1 and TR 2 provided that the BUS TRANS switch is in AUTO', '', 'c', 'TR 3 normally backs up TR 1 and TR 2 provided that the BUS TRANS switch is in AUTO', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5110, '41037', 'Standby A.C. power is available on touch down after a total electrical failure providing', 'The Battery switch is selected to ON and the Standby Power switch is selected to AUTO', 'The Standby Power switch is selected to AUTO', 'The Standby Power switch is selected to BAT', '', 'c', 'The Standby Power switch is selected to BAT', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5111, '41038', 'The APU generator has', 'No Generator drive unit since the APU itself is governed and will maintain a constant generator speed', 'A Generator drive unit which will automatically disconnect when its oil temperature is high', 'A Generator drive unit which will disconnect when the APU Generator drive disconnect switch is activated from the flight deck', '', 'a', 'No Generator drive unit since the APU itself is governed and will maintain a constant generator speed', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5112, '41039', 'If ground power is available and the Ground Service switch on the forward attendant\'s panel is switched on, then power is supplied to', 'The Ground Service bus for utility outlets and cabin lighting only', 'All the aircraft electrical busses', 'The Ground Service bus for utility outlets, cabin lighting and battery charger', '', 'c', 'The Ground Service bus for utility outlets, cabin lighting and battery charger', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5113, '41040', 'An engine electrical generator is rated at', '45 KVA', '35 KVA', '55 KVA', '', 'a', '45 KVA', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5114, '41041', 'The T/R No. 3 disconnect relay automatically opens at glideslope capture to', 'Off-load the battery charger from the 115V AC GND SERVICE Bus', 'Prevent a single bus failure from affecting both the navigation receivers and flight control computers', 'Provide backup power to the Standby DC bus', '', 'b', 'Prevent a single bus failure from affecting both the navigation receivers and flight control computers', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5115, '41042', 'After disconnecting a Generator Drive, its associated oil temperature indicator', 'May show an increase on the IN scale and/or the RISE scale', 'Will immediately show a decrease in temperature', 'Will maintain the same temperature reading', '', 'a', 'May show an increase on the IN scale and/or the RISE scale', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5116, '41043', 'The Battery Switch must be', 'ON or OFF for the GRD PWR Switch to be operable', 'OFF for the GRD PWR Switch to be operable', 'ON for the GRD PWR Switch to be operable', '', 'c', 'ON for the GRD PWR Switch to be operable', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5117, '41044', 'The Battery Switch is ON and the GRD PWR is connected to the aircraft\'s Busses. If the Battery Switch is selected OFF then', 'The GRD POWER AVAILABLE light will extinguish', 'The GRD PWR switch will not automatically disconnect', 'The GRD PWR switch will automatically disconnect', '', 'c', 'The GRD PWR switch will automatically disconnect', 'ERJ-145', 'electrical', 'pilot'),
(5118, '42000', 'The CFM International CFM56-3-B1 is', 'A high bypass ratio turbo fan engine rated at 22,000 pounds of take-off thrust', 'A low bypass ratio turbo fan engine rated at 20,000 pounds of take-off thrust', 'A high bypass ratio turbo fan engine rated at 20,000 pounds of take-off thrust', NULL, 'c', 'A high bypass ratio turbo fan engine rated at 20,000 pounds of take-off thrust', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5119, '42001', 'The CFM56-3 N1 rotor section consists of', 'A single stage fan and a two stage booster section', 'A single stage fan and a nine stage booster section', 'A single stage fan and a three stage booster section', NULL, 'c', 'A single stage fan and a three stage booster section', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5120, '42002', 'The CFM56-3 N1 low pressure turbine consists of', '3 stages', '4 stages', '9 stages', NULL, 'b', '4 stages', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `question_number`, `question`, `option_a`, `option_b`, `option_c`, `option_d`, `correct_option`, `correct_answer`, `aircraft`, `course`, `target_audience`) VALUES
(5121, '42003', 'The CFM56-3 N2 rotor section consists of', 'A nine stage axial flow compressor connected by a through shaft to a single stage high pressure turbine', 'A four stage axial flow compressor connected by a through shaft to a single stage high pressure turbine', 'A nine stage axial flow compressor connected by a through shaft to a four stage high pressure turbine', NULL, 'a', 'A nine stage axial flow compressor connected by a through shaft to a single stage high pressure turbine', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5122, '42004', 'The N1 Manual Set knob', 'When pushed in allows manual setting of the N1 indicator cursor', 'When pulled out enables the FMC input signal to the N1 indicator', 'When pulled out disables the FMC input signal to the N1 indicator', NULL, 'c', 'When pulled out disables the FMC input signal to the N1 indicator', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5123, '42005', 'The Red warning lights on the EIS or conventional Engine instruments will', 'Flash repeatedly until the associated engine parameter is reduced below the limit for that parameter', 'When illuminated, will also illuminate the Master Caution ENG annunciator, until the associated engine parameter is reduced below the limit for that parameter', 'Remain illuminated until the associated engine parameter is reduced below the limit for that parameter', NULL, 'c', 'Remain illuminated until the associated engine parameter is reduced below the limit for that parameter', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5124, '42006', 'The N1 RPM indicator indicates', 'The engine turbine speed in percent of RPM and is used as the primary thrust setting reference', 'The fan speed in percent of RPM and is used as the primary thrust setting reference', 'The engine compressor speed in percent of RPM and is used as the primary thrust setting reference', NULL, 'b', 'The fan speed in percent of RPM and is used as the primary thrust setting reference', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5125, '42007', 'Rotating the N1 Manual Set knob (when pulled) will', 'Set the desired N1 RPM in the N1 Manual Set Indicator (EIS)', 'Set the desired N1 in the upper digital display of the N1 RPM indicator ( EIS ) with the N1 Manual Set Indicator blank', 'Set the desired N1 in the upper digital display of the N1 RPM indicator ( EIS )', NULL, 'a', 'Set the desired N1 RPM in the N1 Manual Set Indicator (EIS)', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5126, '42008', 'Illuminating of the Red warning light above an EGT gauge indicates', 'A warning that an abnormal engine start is occurring', 'The EGT for the associated engine displayed has been reached or exceeded', 'The EGT for either engine has been reached or exceeded', NULL, 'b', 'The EGT for the associated engine displayed has been reached or exceeded', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5127, '42009', 'The N2 RPM indicator displays', 'Low pressure compressor speed in percent of RPM', 'High pressure compressor speed in actual RPM', 'High pressure compressor speed in percent of RPM', NULL, 'c', 'High pressure compressor speed in percent of RPM', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5128, '42010', 'With the Fuel Flow switch selected to the USED position, the digital display on both fuel flow indicators', 'Shows the total fuel consumed per engine since engine start', 'Shows the total fuel consumed per engine since last reset', 'Shows the total fuel consumed per engine per hour', NULL, 'b', 'Shows the total fuel consumed per engine since last reset', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5129, '42011', 'The START VALVE OPEN light (amber) indicates', 'The engine starter valve is open and air is being supplied to the air driven starter', 'The Engine Start switch is in GRD', 'The engine starter valve is open irrespective of air being supplied to the air driven starter', NULL, 'a', 'The engine starter valve is open and air is being supplied to the air driven starter', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5130, '42012', 'The minimum engine oil pressure is', '13psi', '20psi', '25psi', NULL, 'a', '13psi', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5131, '42013', 'Illumination of the OIL FILTER BYPASS light', 'Illuminates the Master Caution ENG annunciator light', 'Indicates the Oil Filter is being bypassed', 'Indicates an impending bypass of the oil Scavenge Filter', NULL, 'c', 'Indicates an impending bypass of the oil Scavenge Filter', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5132, '42014', 'The engine oil pressure is', 'Unregulated and is primarily a function of engine N1 speed', 'Regulated and is primarily a function of engine N2 speed', 'Unregulated and is primarily a function of engine N2 speed', NULL, 'c', 'Unregulated and is primarily a function of engine N2 speed', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5133, '42015', 'The engine vibration indicators', 'Show the engine vibration level throughout all sections of the engine', 'Show the engine vibration level in the turbine section of the engine', 'Show the engine vibration level in the fan section of the engine', NULL, 'c', 'Show the engine vibration level in the fan section of the engine', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5134, '42016', 'During an engine shutdown, the start switch holding solenoid is held in the cutout position until', 'The engine speed falls below 20% N2 RPM', 'The engine start lever is advanced to IDLE again', 'The engine speed falls below 30% N2 RPM', NULL, 'c', 'The engine speed falls below 30% N2 RPM', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5135, '42017', 'The engine Ignition System contains', 'Two high energy AC systems', 'Two high energy DC systems', 'One DC and one AC high energy system', NULL, 'a', 'Two high energy AC systems', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5136, '42018', 'Placing the Engine Start Switch in the GRD position', 'Opens the starter valve, closes the engine bleed air valve and the selected igniter(s) are energised when the Engine Start Lever is placed to IDLE', 'Opens the starter valve, closes the engine bleed air valve and the selected igniter(s) are energized immediately', 'Opens the starter valve, closes the engine bleed air valve and the Right ( Standby AC Bus ) igniter is energized immediately when the Engine Start Lever is placed to IDLE', NULL, 'a', 'Opens the starter valve, closes the engine bleed air valve and the selected igniter(s) are energised when the Engine Start Lever is placed to IDLE', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5137, '42019', 'Placing the Engine Start Switch to the CONT position', 'Provides high energy ignition to the Left igniter when the Engine Start Lever is in the IDLE position', 'Provides high energy ignition to the selected igniter(s) when the Engine Start Lever is in the IDLE position', 'Provides high energy ignition to the selected igniter(s) when the Engine Start Lever is in the IDLE or CUTOFF positions', NULL, 'b', 'Provides high energy ignition to the selected igniter(s) when the Engine Start Lever is in the IDLE position', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5138, '42020', 'Placing the Engine Start switch to the FLT position', 'Provides high energy ignition to both igniters when the Engine Start Lever is positioned to IDLE', 'Opens the starter valve and provides high energy ignition to both igniters when the Engine Start Lever is positioned to IDLE', 'Provides high energy ignition to the selected igniter(s) when the Engine Start Lever is positioned to IDLE', NULL, 'a', 'Provides high energy ignition to both igniters when the Engine Start Lever is positioned to IDLE', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5139, '42021', 'With the Ignition Select switch in the IGN R position', 'Both igniters are selected for use on the right engine', 'The right igniter is selected for use on both engines', 'The right igniter is selected for use on the right engine', NULL, 'b', 'The right igniter is selected for use on both engines', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5140, '42022', 'The Engine Start Lever selected to IDLE during an engine start', 'Energizes the ignition system, mechanically opens the engine fuel shutoff valve in the wing leading edge, and electrically opens the MEC shutoff valve', 'Energizes the ignition system, electrically opens the engine fuel and MEC shutoff valves in the wing leading edge', 'Energizes the ignition system, electrically opens the engine fuel shutoff valve in the wing leading edge, and mechanically opens the MEC shutoff valve', NULL, 'c', 'Energizes the ignition system, electrically opens the engine fuel shutoff valve in the wing leading edge, and mechanically opens the MEC shutoff valve', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5141, '42023', 'The PMC INOP indication is suppressed', 'Below starter cutout engine speed', 'Above starter cutout engine speed', '30 seconds after the engine start lever is positioned to CUTOFF', NULL, 'a', 'Below starter cutout engine speed', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5142, '42024', 'The PMC INOP light', 'Indicates the PMC is inoperative when engine speed is above 46% N2 only', 'Indicates the PMC is selected OFF only', 'Indicates the PMC is inoperative when engine speed is above 46% N2 or the PMC is selected OFF', NULL, 'c', 'Indicates the PMC is inoperative when engine speed is above 46% N2 or the PMC is selected OFF', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5143, '42025', 'The PMC is', 'An electronic system with total authority over the MEC', 'An electronic system with limited authority over the MEC', 'A mechanical system with limited authority over the MEC', NULL, 'b', 'An electronic system with limited authority over the MEC', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5144, '42026', 'The PMC provides', 'A variable thrust climb feature once the thrust lever is set at the beginning of the climb', 'A constant thrust climb feature once the thrust lever is set at the beginning of the climb', 'A constant EGT and Fuel Flow feature once the thrust lever is set at the beginning of the climb', NULL, 'b', 'A constant thrust climb feature once the thrust lever is set at the beginning of the climb', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5145, '42027', 'For detectable failure conditions, the PMC', 'Illuminates the PMC INOP, Master Caution and ENG annunciator lights only', 'Schedules a slow N1 drift over approximately 30 seconds and illuminates the PMC INOP, Master Caution and ENG annunciator lights', 'Schedules a slow N1 drift over approximately 30 seconds and illuminates the PMC INOP light only', NULL, 'b', 'Schedules a slow N1 drift over approximately 30 seconds and illuminates the PMC INOP, Master Caution and ENG annunciator lights', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5146, '42028', 'Illumination of the LOW IDLE light indicates', 'One or both Engine Start Levers is in the CUTOFF position', 'The PMC has failed', 'Either engine is near idle and its MEC is not commanded to maintain high idle RPM in flight, or either engine is below 25% N1 in flight', NULL, 'c', 'Either engine is near idle and its MEC is not commanded to maintain high idle RPM in flight, or either engine is below 25% N1 in flight', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5147, '42029', 'With the thrust levers set at idle, the engines will be in Low Idle', 'When on the ground, except for the first 30 seconds after touchdown', 'When on the ground, except for the first 4 seconds after touchdown', 'At all stages of flight or on the ground', NULL, 'b', 'When on the ground, except for the first 4 seconds after touchdown', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5148, '42030', 'The High Idle RPM in flight is approximately', '45% N1', '32% N1', '22% N1', NULL, 'b', '32% N1', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5149, '42031', 'The Fuel Flow Transmitter is located', 'Inside the MEC', 'Between the First and Second Stage of the engine driven fuel pump', 'Downstream of the MEC Fuel Shutoff Valve', NULL, 'c', 'Downstream of the MEC Fuel Shutoff Valve', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5150, '42032', 'The engine fuel system (not including fuel tank pumps) has', 'One engine driven fuel pump with two stages', 'Two electrical fuel pumps', 'Two single stage engine driven fuel pumps', NULL, 'a', 'One engine driven fuel pump with two stages', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5151, '42033', 'The engine fuel system contains', 'One fuel/oil heat exchanger only', 'One fuel heater and one fuel/oil heat exchanger', 'One fuel heater only', NULL, 'b', 'One fuel heater and one fuel/oil heat exchanger', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5152, '42034', 'Fuel anti-icing is provided for the MEC', 'By the fuel heater using AC electrical power from the Generator Busses', 'By the fuel heater using bleed air', 'By the fuel heater using engine oil', NULL, 'c', 'By the fuel heater using engine oil', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5153, '42035', 'The yellow band on the oil pressure indicator is only valid when', 'After engine start, by the time the engine is stabilized at idle', 'On the ground with Takeoff thrust set', 'At all engine operating conditions', NULL, 'b', 'On the ground with Takeoff thrust set', 'ERJ-145', 'engine', 'pilot'),
(5154, '43000', 'When both Centre Tank Fuel pump switches are turned OFF, the fuel scavenge shut-off valve', 'Opens for 20 minutes allowing fuel pressure from the No. 1 tank forward pump to operate the Centre Tank Scavenge Jet pump, which transfers the remaining centre tank fuel to the No. 1 tank', 'Opens allowing pressure from the No. 1 tank forward pump to operate the Centre Tank Scavenge Jet pump, which transfers the remaining centre tank fuel to the No. 2 tank', 'Closes for 20 minutes allowing fuel pressure from the No. 2 tank forward pump to operate the Centre Tank Scavenge Jet pump, which transfers the remaining centre tank fuel to the No. 2 tank', NULL, 'a', 'Opens for 20 minutes allowing fuel pressure from the No. 1 tank forward pump to operate the Centre Tank Scavenge Jet pump, which transfers the remaining centre tank fuel to the No. 1 tank', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5155, '43001', 'A shut-off system is used during refueling to', 'Automatically close the fuelling valve in each fuel tank when the tank is full', 'Automatically close the Manual Defueling Valve when the wing tanks are full.', 'Prevent refueling pressures in excess of 50 psi', NULL, 'a', 'Automatically close the fuelling valve in each fuel tank when the tank is full', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5156, '43002', 'Fuel Quantity indicators will display', 'Blank if a malfunction occurs', 'An ERR symbol if a malfunction occurs', 'An 88888 reading if a malfunction occurs', NULL, 'b', 'An ERR symbol if a malfunction occurs', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5157, '43003', 'To defuel No. 1 tank', 'Select the No. 1 Main tank fuel pumps ON, the Cross feed valve OPEN and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN', 'Select the No. 1 and No. 2 Main tank fuel pumps ON, the Cross feed valve OPEN and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN.', 'Select the No. 1 Main tank fuel pumps ON, the cross feed valve CLOSED and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN', NULL, 'a', 'Select the No. 1 Main tank fuel pumps ON, the Cross feed valve OPEN and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5158, '43004', 'The Fuel Temperature Indicator reads the temperature of the fuel in', 'The No. 2 tank.', 'The Centre tank', 'The No. 1 tank', NULL, 'c', 'The No. 1 tank', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5159, '43005', 'The manual De-fuelling valve is located', 'Outboard of the No. 1 engine', 'Outboard of the No. 2 engine', 'Inboard of the No. 2 engine', NULL, 'b', 'Outboard of the No. 2 engine', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5160, '43006', 'Dripsticks (or Floatsticks) are installed in', '5 in each main tank', '6 in each main tank', '4 in each main tank', NULL, 'a', '5 in each main tank', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5161, '43007', 'The Fuelling Valve Position Lights on the External Fueling Panel illuminate (blue) when', 'The respective fuelling valve is OPEN and fuel is being transferred into the tank', 'The respective fuelling valve is OPEN', 'The respective fuelling valve is in transit', NULL, 'b', 'The respective fuelling valve is OPEN', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5162, '43008', 'When the APU is inoperative and no external power is available, refueling can be accomplished as follows', 'Battery switch ON, Standby Power switch BAT; the entire fuel system will operate normally', 'Battery switch OFF, Standby Power switch BAT; the entire fuel system will operate normally', 'Battery switch ON, Standby Power switch BAT; the entire fuel system will operate normally, except for the fuel shut-off system', NULL, 'a', 'Battery switch ON, Standby Power switch BAT; the entire fuel system will operate normally', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5163, '43009', 'To defuel No. 2 tank only,', 'Select the No. 2 Main tank fuel pumps ON and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN.', 'Select the No. 2 Main tank fuel pumps ON, the Cross feed valve OPEN and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN', 'Select the No. 1 and No. 2 Main tank fuel pumps ON, the Cross feed valve OPEN and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN', NULL, 'a', 'Select the No. 2 Main tank fuel pumps ON and the Manual Defueling valve OPEN.', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5164, '43010', 'Fuel for the APU is', 'Approximately 164 kg/hr with electrics & bleeds at sea level, decreasing to 17 kg/hr at high altitude and low loads.', 'Not heated.', 'Is recorded on the fuel flow meters', NULL, 'a', 'Approximately 164 kg/hr with electrics & bleeds at sea level, decreasing to 17 kg/hr at high altitude and low loads.', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5165, '43011', 'The Fuel Specification for the CFM56 and APU is', 'DTD 585 and 588', 'DERD 2488 only', 'DERD 2494', NULL, 'c', 'DERD 2494', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5166, '43012', 'The Cross feed valve when OPEN', 'Allows transfer of fuel between wing tanks only', 'Allows fuel transfer from any tank to either engine or APU', 'Closes the Bypass valve in each wing tank', NULL, 'b', 'Allows fuel transfer from any tank to either engine or APU', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5167, '43013', 'With failure of all generators, the centre tank fuel', 'Cannot be used.', 'Will be fed to the main tanks by the centre tank scavenge jet pump', 'Can be used by switching off all wing tank pumps and opening the cross feed valve.', NULL, 'a', 'Cannot be used.', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5168, '43014', 'With no pressure refueling system available, the 737CL can be refueled by', 'Using standard overwing fuelling receptacles for gravity fuelling of the No. 1 tank only. The No. 2 tank can then be filled using the fuel transfer pumps', 'Using standard overwing fuelling receptacles for gravity fuelling of the No. 1 and No. 2 and centre tanks', 'Using standard overwing fuelling receptacles for gravity fuelling of the No. 1 and No. 2 tanks only', NULL, 'c', 'Using standard overwing fuelling receptacles for gravity fuelling of the No. 1 and No. 2 tanks only', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5169, '43015', 'The maximum allowable lateral fuel imbalance between No. 1 and No. 2 tanks is', '453 Kgs for all stages of flight', '746 Kgs for all stages of flight', '453 Kgs for takeoff only', NULL, 'a', '453 Kgs for all stages of flight', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5170, '43016', 'Should the indicated fuel quantity in any main tank be 454 Kgs or less', 'Switch on all main tank fuel pumps and open the cross feed valve', 'Switch on all main tank fuel pumps and close the cross feed valve.', 'Switch off the associated fuel pump if both pump LOW', NULL, 'a', 'Switch on all main tank fuel pumps and open the cross feed valve', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5171, '43017', 'The Cross feed Selector in the OPEN position', 'Connects the engine No 1 and No. 2 fuel feed lines by opening the fuel cross feed and fuel shut-off valves', 'Extinguishes the blue VALVE OPEN light', 'Connects the engine No 1 and No. 2 fuel feed lines by opening the fuel cross feed valve.', NULL, 'c', 'Connects the engine No 1 and No. 2 fuel feed lines by opening the fuel cross feed valve.', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5172, '43018', 'The Centre Tank Fuelling Valve Position light on the External Fuelling Panel is', 'Blue and is illuminated when the centre tank fuelling valve is closed.', 'Red and is extinguished when the centre tank fuelling valve is closed', 'Blue and is extinguished when the centre tank fuelling valve is closed', NULL, 'c', 'Blue and is extinguished when the centre tank fuelling valve is closed', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
(5173, '43019', 'The External Fuelling Panel is located', 'At the Right wing leading edge', 'On the opposite wing to the De-fuelling panel', 'At the Left wing leading edge', NULL, 'a', 'At the Right wing leading edge', 'ERJ-145', 'type_fuel', 'pilot'),
